title: Labor supporter slams penalty cuts as 'retail worker' | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad Is he the new 'Fake Tradie'? Ordinary 'retail worker' introduced by Bill Shorten to attack the penalty rate cuts as a 'disgrace' is a gym-loving Labor Party volunteer Muscle-bound critic of Fair Work Commission's penalty rates decision was seen handing out how-to-vote cards for Labor MP Emma Husar last year Trent Hunter spoke about how the cuts would affect him as a retail worker But his personal Facebook page is littered with photos in a NSW Labor shirt Published: 05:31 GMT, 23 February 2017 | Updated: 08:40 GMT, 23 February 2017 301 shares
